Type: Package
Package: rtestim
Title: Estimate the Effective Reproductive Number with Trend Filtering
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Daniel J.", "McDonald", , "daniel@stat.ubc.ca", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Zhenglun", "Cai", , "zhenglun.cai@stat.ubc.ca", role = "aut"),
    person("Jiaping", "Liu", , "jiaping.liu@stat.ubc.ca", role = "aut")
  )
Description: This package uses Poisson likelihood with 
    trend filtering penalty (a type of regularized nonparametric regression)
    to estimate the effective reproductive number, Rt. This value roughly says 
    "how many new infections will result from each new infection today". 
    Values larger than 1 indicate that an epidemic is growing while those less 
    than 1 indicate decline.
